hopobject.body: I love the theatre whats better celebrex or ibuprofen “America cannot determine the future of Egypt, that’s a task for the Egyptian people. We don’t take sides with any particular party or political figure. I know it’s tempting inside of Egypt to blame the United States or the West or some other outside actor for what’s going wrong. We have been blamed by supporters of Mursi, we have been blamed by the other side as if we are supporters of Mursi. That kind of approach will do nothing to help Egyptians to achieve the future they deserve. We want Egypt to succeed, we want a peaceful, democratic, prosperous Egypt,” Obama said.
